<!-- Pain Points -->
<section class="section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">The Problems Our Clients Face</span>
            <h2>The Hidden Costs of Running a Facility That Handles Waste</h2>
            <p>Recycling and composting facilities are in the business of reducing waste — but they're often drowning in their own compliance and disposal challenges. Here's what we hear from operators every day.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid">
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="droplets"></i></div>
                <h3>Leachate Discharge Fines and Storm Sewer Violations</h3>
                <p>Landfill leachate is one of the most tightly regulated discharges in solid waste management. Surface runoff violations and storm sewer discharge events trigger fines, public scrutiny, and regulatory oversight that escalates quickly.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Sub-surface drip irrigation disposes of leachate beneficially through soil treatment — eliminating discharge pathways and turning a compliance problem into a managed land application program.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="hard-hat"></i></div>
                <h3>Post-Closure Cover Compliance Without Water Access</h3>
                <p>Closed landfill cells require vegetated cover that meets regulatory performance standards — but post-closure sites rarely have reliable water sources or maintenance crews willing to hand-water cover crops across acres of capped cells.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Automated drip irrigation establishes and maintains landfill cap vegetation without staff involvement, and generates the monitoring data regulators require for post-closure certification.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="thermometer"></i></div>
                <h3>Compost Quality Inconsistency from Moisture Variability</h3>
                <p>Compost quality — and cycle time — is directly tied to moisture control. Too dry and decomposition stalls. Too wet and you create anaerobic conditions, odor, and leachate. Windrow moisture management by hand or with sprinklers is imprecise and labor-intensive.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Precision drip irrigation applies the exact moisture volume needed at each windrow — shortening cycles, improving finished compost quality, and reducing the labor cost of manual moisture management.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="wind"></i></div>
                <h3>Facility Dust Violations and Air Permit Exceedances</h3>
                <p>Tipping floors, processing areas, and outdoor stockpiles at recycling facilities generate dust that triggers air quality violations. Water trucks are too imprecise and too expensive to operate continuously throughout the day.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Automated micro-drip dust suppression applies moisture on schedule at problem areas — without trucks, without operators, and without over-wetting materials that need to stay dry.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="trash-2"></i></div>
                <h3>No Compliant Path for Used Drip Tape Disposal</h3>
                <p>At the end of the season, growers and operators are left with hundreds of pounds of used dripline. Burning it is illegal. Landfilling it is expensive. Most of it ends up in the wrong place — and that's becoming a liability as plastic waste regulations tighten.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ ReGen™ closes the loop — used DripSmart dripline is collected, shredded, washed, pelletized, and turned into new driplines. No landfill. No burning. No compliance exposure.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="pain-card">
                <div class="pain-icon"><i data-lucide="waves"></i></div>
                <h3>Buffer Zone and Perimeter Management</h3>
                <p>Facilities near residential areas face community scrutiny over odor, runoff, and visual impact. Buffer zones that aren't properly vegetated and maintained become a recurring source of neighbor complaints and regulatory notices.</p>
                <div class="pain-solution">✓ Automated drip irrigation on buffer strips and perimeter zones establishes dense vegetative cover without manual labor — improving facility appearance and reducing runoff pathways simultaneously.</div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

