                <h3>Compost Windrow Moisture Control</h3>
                <p>Consistent, measurable moisture is the single biggest controllable variable in compost quality and cycle time. Precision drip irrigation on windrows shortens curing time, improves finished product uniformity, and reduces hand watering labor by 80%+.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="wind"></i></div>
                <h3>Facility Dust Suppression</h3>
                <p>Tipping floors, processing areas, and outdoor material stockpiles require continuous moisture management to stay inside air permit limits. Automated micro-drip systems apply moisture on schedule without equipment or operator involvement.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="sprout"></i></div>
                <h3>Landfill Cap &amp; Post-Closure Vegetation</h3>
                <p>Establishing and maintaining vegetative cover on closed landfill cells is a long-term compliance obligation that most facilities manage manually. Automated drip systems eliminate that labor dependency and provide the performance documentation regulators require.</p>
            </div>
